<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6866ea0-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s8901"><num value="8901">§ 8901.</num><heading> Freight vessels</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">A freight vessel of less than 100 gross tons as measured under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s14502">section 14502 of this title</ref>, or an alternate tonnage measured under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s14302">section 14302 of this title</ref> as prescribed by the Secretary under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s14104">section 14104 of this title</ref> shall be operated by an individual licensed by the Secretary to operate that type of vessel in the particular geographic area, under prescribed regulations.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf6866ea1-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/555">97 Stat. 555</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/104/324/tVII/s733">Pub. L. 104–324, title VII, § 733</ref>, <date date="1996-10-19">Oct. 19, 1996</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/110/3941">110 Stat. 3941</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idf6866ea2-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">
