<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section 8901 requires that a freight vessel of less than 100 gross tons be operated by a licensed individual for that type vessel and for a particular geographic area.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idf6866ea5-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idf6866ea6-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1996—<ref href="/us/pl/104/324">Pub. L. 104–324</ref> inserted “as measured under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s14502">section 14502 of this title</ref>, or an alternate tonnage measured under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s14302">section 14302 of this title</ref> as prescribed by the Secretary under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s14104">section 14104 of this title</ref>” after “100 gross tons”.</p>
</note>
